      The Pac-12 officially acknowledged that its officiating crew and replay officials in the game between UCLA and Hawai'i on Saturday missed a targeting call. It's not uncommon for the conference to admits mistakes like this, but it took it a step further in part of its official release, stating: "Additionally, during the UCLA v. Hawaii broadcast on Pac-12 Networks, the play in question was erroneously described by the Pac-12's head of officiating [David Coleman]."
